    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ae5da226_c766c98d",
        "filename": "src/gpu/glsl/GrGLSLFragmentShaderBuilder.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 119,
      "author": {
        "id": 5633
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-03-25T17:49:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We could, but I have a few concerns about that:\n\n1) (Main issue) SkSL doesn\u0027t know the sample locations, and the query for sample locations is an API-level feature. So this means we would have to develop a mechanism to tell SkSL the sample locations, AND we would still have to take care to include the sample locations in our shader keys when necessary.\n\n2) The usage pattern is quite specialized in how you are able to specify the gradient yourself. It would make more sense to be a language feature in my mind if it always used HW derivatives, but since you can specify your own gradient (or not), I feel like it kind of fits being a function we define ourselves.\n\n3) It\u0027s approximate. Other multisample language features like interpolateAtSample() are more accurate.",
      "parentUuid": "5c04a89a_f475d7a7",
      "revId": "8a7f4dbf364a58465350f2b134974b25d5b5a230",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b0a1bafd_a86244a2",
        "filename": "src/gpu/glsl/GrGLSLFragmentShaderBuilder.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 119,
      "author": {
        "id": 5085
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-03-25T21:02:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "1) I don\u0027t see why we couldn\u0027t use uniforms and just put the number of samples in the key. This doesn\u0027t seem like it should be prohibitive to adding general sample mask support to sksl. We have something like this for the Skia device space -\u003e NDC conversion.\n\n2/3) Maybe this particular shouldn\u0027t be a builder feature at all then and just be implemented as a helper (assuming we need it in more than one place)?\n\nIf we\u0027re envisioning using sample masks more often throughout our code I kind of think we should figure out they fit in with where we see the sksl system evolving rather than layering on more old-style builder stuff that we will have to deal with later. I\u0027m ok with not doing all that now but I don\u0027t want to just keep kicking the can down the road and accumulate more technical debt without a plan to address it.\n\nEthan, does this make sense to you or am I making something out of nothing?",
      "parentUuid": "ae5da226_c766c98d",
      "revId": "8a7f4dbf364a58465350f2b134974b25d5b5a230",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a9a7dd05_d878d51d",
        "filename": "src/gpu/glsl/GrGLSLFragmentShaderBuilder.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 119,
      "author": {
        "id": 5633
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-03-25T23:33:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So uniforms would work, my only question is whether it would be slower than hard-coded sample locations. It would probably be fine, but is probably worth benchmarking before we commit to it.\n\nAlthough, even if we use uniforms, we still have to remember to add the sample count to the key. So I\u0027m not sure how much it helps- either way we have to know what SkSL will do behind the scenes and then account for it in the shader key. Also, per the spec, the actual number of samples in effect doesn\u0027t have to match the number of samples we requested when we created the surface. So either way we also have to query info from the driver and pass it along to SkSL.\n\nRE: helper- that would work fine. Although, since the sample mask is a builder feature I\u0027m not too concerned about this sample mask/gradient helper also being on that class. Do we want to talk about removing sample mask from the builder as well? I suppose we could pass that name around and combine it between stages like we do coverage.",
      "parentUuid": "b0a1bafd_a86244a2",
      "revId": "8a7f4dbf364a58465350f2b134974b25d5b5a230",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
